<sn><md>#### Using a `for` Loop

A `for` loop can iterate through the array to determine the minimum or maximum value.

```javascript
  var maxValue = myArray[0];
  for (var i = 1; i &lt; myArray.length; i++) {
      var currentValue = myArray[i];
      if (currentValue &gt; maxValue) {
          maxValue = currentValue;
      }
  }
```
</md></sn><sn><md>### Using `Array.prototype.reduce`

The `reduce()` method can find the minimum or maximum value in an array.

```javascript
  var myArray = [1, 2, 3, 4];

  myArray.reduce(function(a, b) {
      return Math.min(a, b);
  }); // 1

  myArray.reduce(function(a, b) {
      return Math.max(a, b);
  }); // 4
```

**With Arrow Functions (Version â‰¥ 6)**
  ```javascript
